                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "<p rend=\"align(right)\"><placeName>Cincinnati</placeName>\n                <date>September 16<hi rend=\"sup\">th</hi> 1862</date>.</p>\n            <p>Reverend Sir,</p>\n            <p>In consequence of the advertisement<lb/> of the Hebrew Ed. Society of your<lb/> city\n                I have this day directed a letter<lb/> to <persName>Mr. I. Binswanger</persName>, in\n                which<lb/> I reported him on the course of studies<lb/> I pursued, the testimonials\n                I hold<lb/> and how long, where and in what<lb/> occupation I spent the time of\n                my<lb/> sojourn in this country.</p>\n            <p>After taking the liberty of referring<lb/> also to you, Rev. Sir, I applied for<lb/>\n                the vacant situation, mentioned in<lb/> the above advertisement, provided<lb/>\n                stipulations and salary be acceptable.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">Now, Rev. Sir, I know the great<lb/> authority you exercise and the\n                great<lb/> influence you have with the Board<lb/> of the above school. I\n                likewise<lb/> flatter myself to be known to</p>"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3kp7vb71/canvas/p1"
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
